{
  "texts": [
    "The AB 2 alloying elements, and hydrogen storage capacity (wt.%) are provided in the dataset.",
    "To estimate the hydrogen storage capacity in the AB 2 metal alloys, 22 alloying elements including Mg, Zr, Ce, Mn, Sn, Mo, Cr, V, Ni, Fe, La, Al, C, Ti, Gd, B, Si, W, Cu, Co, Nb, and Ho are considered as the input variables.",
    "Meanwhile, the associated hydrogen storage capacity is utilized as an output variable.",
    "To attain a highly accurate model, 25% of the total data was separated randomly as the testing dataset while the remaining 75% of the data was employed for training the model.",
    "R 2, standard deviation (STD), mean-square error (MSE), root-mean-square error (RMSE), and mean relative error (MRE) are the statistical factors that can be used to quantify the developed model accuracy [63] [64] [65]."
  ]
}